Three members of a gang who attempted to rob the branch of an old generation bank in Okeho, Oyo State were on Wednesday set ablaze by an angry mob. The robbers attacked the bank at about 3pm with a dynamite to gain access. It was however not yet clear if they succeeded in gaining access to the coffers. Oyo Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO) Gbenga Fadeyi informed the robbers were repelled by armed policemen deployed to counter them. According to him, the robbers were conveyed in an 18-seater bus to the bank. As soon as their attempt to rob the bank failed, he claimed they took to their heels but were pursued by policemen, local hunters and other concerned individuals. Speeding under pressure, Fadeyi, a Superintendent of Police, said, their bus summersaulted. He added a mob swooped and set the three of them ablaze. He described the incident as a failed robbery attempt, promising to give more details. But sources in the area said the robbers were ambushed and set ablaze by local hunters. Fadeyi said police were on the trail of other members of the gang who escaped. The Nation Zaria  -  The Police on Thursday confirmed the killing of three suspected armed robbers by a mob at Tudun-Saibu village in Soba Local Government Area of Kaduna State. Alhaji Mohammed Shehu, Police Area Commander, told the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Zaria on Friday, that two other members of… March 18, 2016 In "Metro" By Peter Okolie Onitsha (Anambra) -  A suspected robber was on Wednesday set ablaze by irate youths in Nkpor, near Onitsha, following alleged robbery attack on a businessman along Owerri-Awka road in the area. An eyewitness told the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) that the victim had just finished withdrawing… July 19, 2017 In "Metro" Police Nab 2 Suspected Bank Robbers in Anambra July 2, 2017 In "Top Stories"